"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-siya-rachel-kolisi-tatjana-smith-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bb'Family business': Siya Kolisi celebrates Tatjana Smith  Springboks skipper Siya Kolisi celebrated his wife's sister-in-law Tatjana Smith, who won gold at the Paris Olympics 2024.  Springboks skipper Siya Kolisi showed his wife's sister-in-law, Tatjana Smith some love after she won gold medals at the Paris Olympics, via an Instagram post on Thursday 22 August.  Springboks skipperSiya Kolisi is always the biggest fan of all South African \\\"national treasures\\\". He often takes to Instagram to celebrate South Africans, and this time, he showed his wife - Rachel Kolisi's sister-in-law Tatjana Smith after she won gold at the Paris Olympics 2024.  Tatjana is married to Rachel's brother, Joel Smith. The pair tied the knot in November 2023. Siya used a bible quote in the caption of the post.  \\\"The LORD has done great things for us, and we are filled with joy. ~Psalm 126:3. FAMILY BUSINESS \\u2764\\ufe0f\\ud83d\\ude4f\\ud83c\\udffe,\\\" she wrote.  A post shared by Siya Kolisi (@siyakolisi)  This comes after Rachel also took to Instagram to celebrate Tatjana and her big wins.  \\\"I can not believe she's my sister-in-law \\ud83e\\udd79.  A South African gem, I am so proud of you\\u00a0@tatjanaschoen\\u00a0for the medals yes, but mostly for the sacrifices, hard decisions, and commitment to our good Lord. \\u2764\\ufe0f,\\\" she wrote.  \\\"Spent the day with our\\u00a0@mercedesbenzsa\\u00a0and\\u00a0@kolisi_foundation\\u00a0fam today doing a power 2 you activation with a group of high school girls. (This meant we could sneak in a lunch with Tats and\\u00a0@jcsmith7\\u00a0). A beautiful day in JHB with beautiful people \\ud83d\\ude4f\\ud83c\\udffc,\\\" she continued.  A post shared by Rachel Kolisi (@rachelkolisi)  Take a look at Rachel reflecting onadopting Siya's siblings.  The Olympic swimmer announced that she was retiring at the Paris Olympics 2024 on 1 August. Tatjana expressed that she is excited for a life outside of swimming. She went on to say that achievements fall away and people are remembered for who they are and bringing joy.  I am looking forward to my life outside of swimming. It was an amazing battle and I have never raced Kate (Douglass) in an Olympic final before. I could not have asked for a better way to end my career in a very tough battle. I have always loved competing,\\\" she said.  \\\"Achievements fall away. You are remembered for who you are and I want to be remembered for bringing people joy. Swimming is a part of a season in your life and now I am excited to live life,\\\" she said confirming her retirement.  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to\\u00a0060 011 021 1  You can also follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor the latest news.  'The South African' is hiring! Freelance writer positions available. Send us your CV  The draw for Rugby World Cup 2027 will take place in Sydney, Australia on Wednesday, 3 December at 11:00 (SA time).  Today's Daily Lotto jackpot stands at an estimated R550 000. If you want to win your share of the jackpot, you have to play!  Faberge's The Winter Egg, fetched a record \\u00a322.9 million (R518 million) at auction on Tuesday, Christie's said.  Former Pirates star Phumudzo Manenzhe has discussed the exclusion of Thapelo Morena from Bafana Bafana's AFCON 2025 squad.  Kaizer Chiefs will play their penultimate match of 2025 on Wednesday, 3 December when they visit Chippa United in Gqeberha.  Secures a NEW shopping bag? Woolworths has seemingly disassociated itself with the testimony of 'tenderpreneur' Vusi 'Cat Matlala\\u2026    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about 